- Very nice, yes.

265
00:23:04,483 --> 00:23:07,509
This is good beer.
I hardly ever drink beer anymore.

266
00:23:07,619 --> 00:23:08,813
Thank goodness.

267
00:23:11,323 --> 00:23:13,348
And Karl? Does he still drink?

268
00:23:13,458 --> 00:23:15,119
How should I know?

269
00:23:16,795 --> 00:23:18,490
Karl never drank very much.

270
00:23:20,165 --> 00:23:22,793
Oh, yes he did.
Like a fish for a while.

271
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:26,598
That's absolutely not true.
- Nonsense!

272
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:28,764
Does Karli have a girlfriend in Tokyo?

273
00:23:29,174 --> 00:23:31,438
Mama, you call him all the time.
Ask him next time:

274
00:23:31,543 --> 00:23:34,478
"So Karli, how's it going?
Still boozing and what about chicks?"

275
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,405
So, what'll we do now?

276
00:23:38,283 --> 00:23:39,841
What would you like to?

277
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:47,822
You're both probably tired
and want to go straight to bed.

278
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:54,698
It's not even six?

279
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,062
We could cook something.

280
00:23:57,803 --> 00:24:00,067
No, Franzi, you've done enough.

281
00:24:03,809 --> 00:24:04,935
Let's go, Rudi.

282
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:16,213
Want us to drive you home?

283
00:24:16,321 --> 00:24:17,253
No.

284
00:24:17,989 --> 00:24:20,184
Franzi!

285
00:24:20,292 --> 00:24:22,590
Let us take the S-Bahn...

286
00:24:22,694 --> 00:24:28,655
a little big city flair
for us country bumpkins...

287
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:29,927
Take care.

288
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:33,636
Come here.

289
00:24:36,908 --> 00:24:37,875
See you tomorrow.

290
00:24:38,844 --> 00:24:40,004
Tomorrow?

291
00:24:40,112 --> 00:24:42,080
We have a date.
- Aha.

292
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:46,614
Papa!

293
00:24:47,519 --> 00:24:48,747
So long!
- Bye!

294
00:24:54,359 --> 00:24:55,485
Bye, Mama.

295
00:25:16,114 --> 00:25:17,046
Are you coming?

296
00:25:18,049 --> 00:25:19,243
Let's have some wine.

297
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:21,342
Let's drink something. Come on.

298
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:26,987
I'm awful...
- No!

299
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:29,686
Where do we have to go? Herrmannsdorf?

300
00:25:29,795 --> 00:25:30,955
What?

301
00:25:31,062 --> 00:25:33,758
Berlin Center. Where is it?
Has to be in the center somewhere.

302
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:35,457
Give me some change.

303
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:36,534
How much?

304
00:25:36,635 --> 00:25:39,968
The train's leaving! You'd know it!

305
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:41,805
It won't go in.
- Try it again...

306
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:44,372
It won't take it. How am I
supposed to buy a ticket?

307
00:25:44,476 --> 00:25:45,534
Try this...

308
00:25:46,878 --> 00:25:49,369
It won't go in. It doesn't work.

309
00:25:49,481 --> 00:25:51,574
That's Berlin for you.
- Rudi, I think you need paper money.

310
00:25:51,683 --> 00:25:55,141
They're out of their minds.
A machine and no tickets come out.

311
00:25:59,591 --> 00:26:04,221
Wait... Berlin AB, just what I said.

312
00:26:04,329 --> 00:26:05,125
What now?

313
00:26:05,230 --> 00:26:08,165
We need one more.

314
00:26:08,266 --> 00:26:10,461
So now we have one ticket
for either you or me or what?

315
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:14,562
Read what it says "Two people
can't use one ticket." Look here!

316
00:26:14,673 --> 00:26:17,836
You can't even pay here.

317
00:26:17,943 --> 00:26:22,004
Am I supposed to walk? Or you?
Or one of us doesn't pay or what?

318
00:26:22,113 --> 00:26:24,013
Rudi, don't get so excited.

319
00:26:24,816 --> 00:26:26,579
I'm not excited. I'm furious.

320
00:26:39,631 --> 00:26:41,030
I think I want to go home.

321
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:43,198
Oh, Rudi...

322
00:26:43,301 --> 00:26:44,962
The kids don't have any time for us.

323
00:26:50,141 --> 00:26:52,735
The Baltic isn't far.
- Hmm?

324
00:26:54,179 --> 00:26:56,909
When was the last time
we were at the beach?

325
00:26:57,015 --> 00:26:58,175
At the beach?

326
00:26:58,283 --> 00:27:00,148
I can't remember either.

327
00:27:00,252 --> 00:27:02,982
1987? With the kids?

328
00:27:03,088 --> 00:27:04,680
Or was that Lake Garda?

329
00:27:06,725 --> 00:27:08,215
You want to go to the beach?

330
00:27:09,094 --> 00:27:11,221
Yes, would you?

331
00:27:11,329 --> 00:27:15,425
If you want to.
- But what do you want?

332
00:27:16,101 --> 00:27:18,228
I always do whatever you say...

333
00:31:38,496 --> 00:31:40,862
The beach isn't what
it used to be, either.

334
00:31:42,667 --> 00:31:46,068
You old grouch. Aren't you cold?

335
00:31:46,171 --> 00:31:47,331
You know what?

336
00:31:47,438 --> 00:31:48,632
Slip in there.

337
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:51,573
What?
- It's warm. Go on.

338
00:31:51,676 --> 00:31:55,077
Tomorrow we'll get up early
and take a long walk on the beach.

339
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:57,375
What? You want to take a walk?

340
00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:58,915
Wonderful!

341
00:32:01,119 --> 00:32:04,111
I'd like my ashes to
be scattered at sea.

342
00:32:06,791 --> 00:32:08,190
What makes you say that?

343
00:32:08,293 --> 00:32:10,727
Nothing. Don't you ever
think about that?

344
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:14,489
Really? Well, I do every now and then.
How much time we have left...

345
00:32:16,634 --> 00:32:17,498
Rudi...

346
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:20,366
You're right.
One ought not think about it...

347
00:32:21,372 --> 00:32:22,896
We've been lucky so far.

348
00:32:25,109 --> 00:32:30,046
Assuming we didn't have much time
left, what would you like to do?

349
00:32:31,115 --> 00:32:32,844
Ah, that line: Live every day
as if it were your last.

350
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:34,851
What nonsense.
What else should you do?

351
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:38,286
Let me tell you: I wouldn't
do anything differently. Nothing.

352
00:32:38,389 --> 00:32:40,823
I'd go to work in the morning
and come home to you in the evening.

353
00:32:40,925 --> 00:32:42,859
That's what I'd do.

354
00:32:42,961 --> 00:32:44,121
Yes.

355
00:32:56,541 --> 00:32:58,008
Can't you sleep?

356
00:32:58,109 --> 00:33:00,236
The surf is so loud.

357
00:33:10,154 --> 00:33:13,089
And now that.
- Come on, Rudi!

358
00:33:15,860 --> 00:33:16,758
It's nice.

359
00:33:26,337 --> 00:33:28,965
You are and always will be loony.

360
00:33:30,208 --> 00:33:31,539
Oh, come on!

361
00:33:31,643 --> 00:33:32,974
What on earth are you doing?

362
00:33:33,077 --> 00:33:34,601
Come on. You can't sleep anyway.

363
00:33:34,712 --> 00:33:36,475
Cut it out!

364
00:33:37,548 --> 00:33:40,415
Dancing in the middle of the night?
Other people are asleep.

365
00:34:51,956 --> 00:34:55,084
What's with you?
- Nothing. Nothing at all.

366
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:31,952
What's wrong? Have you had enough?

367
00:35:32,063 --> 00:35:33,587
Didn't you sleep well?

368
00:35:34,966 --> 00:35:37,662
I didn't but you did.
- Me? Not one second.

369
00:35:37,769 --> 00:35:39,828
You slept like a log.

370
00:35:43,241 --> 00:35:44,970
Let's go home.

371
00:35:45,076 --> 00:35:46,839
We've seen Berlin,
we've seen the Baltic,

372
00:35:46,944 --> 00:35:48,878
and we've seen the children.
Let's go home.

373
00:35:50,114 --> 00:35:52,708
I thought you'd be glad to
see your children.

374
00:35:54,185 --> 00:35:56,176
I don't know them. They don't know me.

375
00:35:58,589 --> 00:36:00,989
Our children are better than most.

376
00:36:01,092 --> 00:36:02,855
Yes, we're fortunate.

377
00:36:03,895 --> 00:36:06,125
We have each other.
That's real happiness.

378
00:36:18,376 --> 00:36:19,308
What is it?

379
00:36:20,611 --> 00:36:21,407
Nothing.

380
00:36:22,447 --> 00:36:23,880
I just didn't get
a good night's sleep.

381
00:36:23,981 --> 00:36:26,245
Whenever I woke up
you were sound asleep.

382
00:37:41,392 --> 00:37:45,294
How calm the sea is.

383
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:49,229
As if was always that way.

384
00:37:49,333 --> 00:37:51,494
It's time to rise and shine!
Come on! Get up you lazybones!

385
00:37:53,538 --> 00:37:55,267
Trudi...

386
00:38:00,077 --> 00:38:02,272
Trudi...

387
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:37,679
Papa, Karl's here.

388
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:42,251
The sea is so calm.

389
00:38:52,563 --> 00:38:53,359
Come on.

390
00:39:48,286 --> 00:39:50,652
I can't stand her lying
in that box in there.

391
00:39:50,755 --> 00:39:55,124
I haven't seen her for so long
and now I'll never see her again.

392
00:39:56,394 --> 00:40:00,558
I should've visited her.
Or at least flown her to Tokyo.

393
00:40:00,665 --> 00:40:03,065
I never did anything for her.

394
00:40:04,268 --> 00:40:05,997
And now there's nothing I can do.

395
00:40:08,539 --> 00:40:10,439
We have to look after Papa now.

396
00:40:11,008 --> 00:40:13,602
And how am I supposed to do that?
- I understand.

397
00:41:15,039 --> 00:41:16,529
We never went to the beach
when we were kids.

398
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:17,868
No, always to the mountains, right?

399
00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:19,169
We were in Italy once.

400
00:41:19,276 --> 00:41:20,766
But not at the beach.
- Lake Garda.

401
00:41:21,512 --> 00:41:22,774
Grosglockner. We took the Grosglockner
pass over the Alps, right, Papa?

402
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,507
Yeah. We all got carsick

403
00:41:24,615 --> 00:41:27,140
but Mama had a plastic bag
for each of us.

404
00:41:27,251 --> 00:41:29,116
She was so full of life back then.

405
00:41:31,389 --> 00:41:32,549
How old was she?

406
00:41:32,656 --> 00:41:34,487
A little older than we are now.

407
00:41:34,592 --> 00:41:38,187
She devoted almost her
entire life to you kids and me.

408
00:41:38,996 --> 00:41:40,759
She wouldn't have put it that way.

409
00:41:43,167 --> 00:41:44,634
Want me to go with you?

410
00:41:46,370 --> 00:41:50,670
It's just not right. It's not fair.
She can't just leave him alone with us.

411
00:41:50,775 --> 00:41:52,834
I don't think she planned it like that.
- Yes, I know.

412
00:41:52,943 --> 00:41:55,138
Mama would've been able to
get along... No problem there.

413
00:41:55,246 --> 00:41:58,409
But him? What are we
supposed to do with him?

414
00:42:00,551 --> 00:42:02,178
When are you flying back?

415
00:42:02,286 --> 00:42:04,948
I can't stay long. My flight leaves
tomorrow afternoon from Berlin.

416
00:42:05,055 --> 00:42:06,283
We have to get back, too.

417
00:42:06,390 --> 00:42:08,085
So do we.
The kids are at the neighbors.

418
00:42:08,192 --> 00:42:09,420
Who has the bag?

419
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:10,357
What bag?

420
00:42:10,461 --> 00:42:12,361
The bag with her things. I'd like to
have the kimono if you all don't mind.

421
00:42:12,463 --> 00:42:13,361
She always used to
have it on in the kitchen. No.

422
00:42:13,464 --> 00:42:14,328
Yes.

423
00:42:14,965 --> 00:42:17,160
It's all over. And it's impossible
to even imagine beforehand.

424
00:42:31,215 --> 00:42:33,979
If I had known
it would end so suddenly,

425
00:42:36,921 --> 00:42:40,357
I would have been nicer to her.

426
00:42:41,826 --> 00:42:45,421
Papa, nobody can know that.

427
00:42:47,131 --> 00:42:49,122
Thanks for us to be able to
sit here like this.

428
00:42:49,233 --> 00:42:51,827
She would have been
very happy you came, Karl.

429
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:55,933
What are you going to do now?

430
00:42:58,042 --> 00:42:59,976
I'll have to get used to it.

431
00:43:00,077 --> 00:43:01,772
Don't worry about me.

432
00:43:07,117 --> 00:43:08,106
Thanks.

433
00:43:10,054 --> 00:43:11,521
Emma, give me a little more wine.

434
00:43:12,356 --> 00:43:13,789
Excuse me.

435
00:45:32,830 --> 00:45:35,458
My condolences.
- Thank you.

436
00:45:35,566 --> 00:45:37,534
And this must be Karolin.

437
00:45:37,635 --> 00:45:41,901
No, no, Karolin is in Berlin.
And our youngest is in Japan.

438
00:45:42,006 --> 00:45:43,871
Ah, yes. And Klaus? Where is Klaus?

439
00:45:44,575 --> 00:45:46,805
He has a very important meeting.
- I see.

440
00:45:47,378 --> 00:45:49,403
My condolences.

441
00:45:49,513 --> 00:45:53,142
My condolences. My condolences.

442
00:45:53,784 --> 00:45:57,447
The dance performance was
what she enjoyed most in Berlin.

443
00:45:57,554 --> 00:45:59,454
She said she'd never met
a nicer girl than you.

444
00:45:59,556 --> 00:46:02,992
I'm not that nice. I don't know
why she thought that of me.

445
00:46:03,093 --> 00:46:05,653
She told me about how
she always wanted to dance,

446
00:46:06,864 --> 00:46:09,992
to become a really good Butoh dancer,
more than anything else in her life...

447
00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:13,900
and how she would've liked to
go to Japan so much to study it there

448
00:46:14,004 --> 00:46:18,236
and how everything
turned out differently

449
00:46:18,742 --> 00:46:21,176
and that it was a good life but...
Not that you think that she wasn't happy.

450
00:46:21,278 --> 00:46:25,146
No... I thought...
maybe there's another woman in her...

451
00:46:25,249 --> 00:46:28,275
that nobody saw...

452
00:46:28,385 --> 00:46:31,115
and I saw that other person...
that's all...

453
00:46:58,082 --> 00:46:59,049
That's her?

454
00:47:01,118 --> 00:47:06,488
I didn't like it.
It was so... so extreme.

455
00:47:06,590 --> 00:47:10,651
It embarrassed me...
I didn't want her to keep it up...

456
00:47:12,062 --> 00:47:14,257
We locked her up in here.

457
00:47:15,065 --> 00:47:16,999
But she was happy here.

458
00:47:17,701 --> 00:47:18,690
For sure.

459
00:47:20,237 --> 00:47:21,431
I don't know.

460
00:47:26,343 --> 00:47:27,241
Goodbye.

461
00:47:39,123 --> 00:47:40,920
All the best.
- Thanks.

462
00:47:41,592 --> 00:47:43,116
Have a good trip!
- Okay!

463
00:48:34,545 --> 00:48:37,537
One hundred Views of Mt. Fuji.

464
00:49:09,913 --> 00:49:12,711
Trudi, where are you?

465
00:49:14,952 --> 00:49:16,419
Where?

466
00:49:59,396 --> 00:50:00,761
Papa.
- Ah!

467
00:50:00,864 --> 00:50:03,196
I thought you'd forgotten me. Hi.

468
00:50:03,300 --> 00:50:06,064
I couldn't get away earlier.

469
00:50:06,169 --> 00:50:08,262
How are you? Was the flight okay?
- Fine.

470
00:50:33,163 --> 00:50:34,221
Papa, come on.

471
00:51:02,559 --> 00:51:04,254
You have to take your shoes off.

472
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:08,259
Oh, yes.

473
00:51:11,068 --> 00:51:11,966
Wait...

474
00:51:18,775 --> 00:51:19,469
There.

475
00:51:19,576 --> 00:51:21,476
I brought my own.
- Okay.

476
00:51:36,426 --> 00:51:37,893
It's not exactly big.

477
00:51:38,729 --> 00:51:39,753
No.

478
00:51:48,305 --> 00:51:49,397
Want something to drink?

479
00:52:02,252 --> 00:52:04,345
Mama always sent you this.

480
00:52:04,454 --> 00:52:08,515
You can't get bread like this
in Japan and the sausages.

481
00:52:08,625 --> 00:52:14,120
And these, two flavors.

482
00:52:14,231 --> 00:52:15,493
Papa, I have to get back to the office.

483
00:52:15,599 --> 00:52:17,760
What exactly do you do?

484
00:52:17,868 --> 00:52:19,802
I've never quite understood...

485
00:52:19,903 --> 00:52:23,896
Nice of you to ask after five years.
I crunch numbers.

486
00:52:24,007 --> 00:52:25,736
What you do with garbage fees.
I do pretty much the same thing as you.

487
00:52:32,282 --> 00:52:36,810
Look... Radio, air conditioner,
satellite receiver, TV.

488
00:52:37,621 --> 00:52:39,054
See you this evening, okay?

489
00:52:40,891 --> 00:52:42,483
I'll be back around six.

490
00:53:37,914 --> 00:53:41,372
My dear Karl,
here's the second stanza:

491
00:53:41,485 --> 00:53:46,184
Oh, let it hover there
until it meets its end

492
00:53:46,289 --> 00:53:52,524
lts heaven lasts forever
It's life one day to make amends

493
00:54:51,721 --> 00:54:54,417
Want something else?
- No, it's fine.

494
00:54:55,892 --> 00:54:58,759
We'll think something out for you
tomorrow. I have to go out later tonight.

495
00:55:01,097 --> 00:55:01,654
Okay.

496
00:55:01,765 --> 00:55:06,600
I'm sorry that I have such little time
but I didn't have much warning.

497
00:55:06,703 --> 00:55:10,070
I don't want to get on your nerves.
- Come on, don't even say that.

498
00:55:15,278 --> 00:55:18,179
Why didn't the two of you
ever visit me?

499
00:55:23,486 --> 00:55:25,477
We thought we had time.

500
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:34,328
I think I kept your mother from
what was most important to her.

501
00:55:36,967 --> 00:55:38,867
You can't do things for the dead.

502
00:55:39,736 --> 00:55:41,294
Papa...

503
00:57:00,917 --> 00:57:04,478
Look, here's some yen.
I'll pick you up later.

504
00:57:04,587 --> 00:57:07,488
Don't move from here.
I don't want you to get lost. Look,

505
00:57:08,491 --> 00:57:10,618
I work over there.
- Which building?

506
00:57:10,727 --> 00:57:13,161
Next to the black one.
So, I'll pick you up later. Bye.

507
00:57:29,212 --> 00:57:31,612
Uh... beer.

508
00:57:48,965 --> 00:57:49,693
Thank you.

509
00:58:24,467 --> 00:58:26,401
Ahungu what?

510
01:00:45,508 --> 01:00:48,500
Nein, I'm, I'm not understand.

511
01:00:53,182 --> 01:00:54,672
Oh, no, es ist, it's good, it's good.

512
01:02:07,390 --> 01:02:10,188
Hey! Where were you? Are you crazy?

513
01:02:10,293 --> 01:02:13,694
I was so worried.
I thought I'd lost you for good.

514
01:02:13,796 --> 01:02:15,525
Unbelievable!

515
01:02:15,632 --> 01:02:18,157
The doorbells, I couldn't read them.

516
01:02:18,267 --> 01:02:19,632
Who told you to go anywhere?

517
01:02:19,736 --> 01:02:21,101
You can't read anything here.

518
01:02:21,204 --> 01:02:22,432
I told you to stay put.
- I don't understand anything.

