01:42:38,568 --> 01:42:39,728
Great.

794
01:43:20,577 --> 01:43:21,805
...Beer...

795
01:44:40,290 --> 01:44:42,781
Uh, what is this?
- Chicken.

796
01:44:42,892 --> 01:44:44,257
Hm?
- Chicken.

797
01:44:45,128 --> 01:44:46,095
Ah.

798
01:44:47,397 --> 01:44:49,160
Hendl in German.
- Hendl...

799
01:44:54,237 --> 01:44:57,729
No!

800
01:51:09,545 --> 01:51:12,912
Rudi? Rudi?

801
01:51:13,983 --> 01:51:15,143
Rudi!

802
01:51:23,626 --> 01:51:24,957
Rudi!

803
01:51:32,668 --> 01:51:33,794
Rudi!

804
01:51:38,307 --> 01:51:39,865
Rudi!

805
01:52:30,893 --> 01:52:36,024
(FOR YOU, YU, FROM RUDI)

806
01:55:28,971 --> 01:55:31,838
Thank you for everything
you did for my father.

807
01:55:32,842 --> 01:55:34,833
I did not do anything.

808
01:55:36,846 --> 01:55:38,575
Your father happy now.

809
01:55:40,249 --> 01:55:41,409
You think so?

810
01:55:54,964 --> 01:55:58,331
Your father. Your mother.

811
01:56:02,772 --> 01:56:04,034
Aha.

812
01:57:02,364 --> 01:57:07,324
My condolences.

813
01:57:14,076 --> 01:57:15,941
We're orphans now,
in less than half a year.

814
01:57:16,045 --> 01:57:17,205
It's all like a dream.

815
01:57:17,313 --> 01:57:18,871
I can't even believe I'm here.

816
01:57:18,981 --> 01:57:21,848
What you told us is so off the wall.

817
01:57:21,951 --> 01:57:23,714
It doesn't sound like Papa.

818
01:57:23,819 --> 01:57:25,684
He couldn't take Mama's death.

819
01:57:25,788 --> 01:57:27,483
In a hotel.

820
01:57:28,190 --> 01:57:29,521
With an eighteen-year-old girl.

821
01:57:29,625 --> 01:57:30,819
In women's clothes.

822
01:57:30,926 --> 01:57:32,120
Mama's clothes.

823
01:57:34,029 --> 01:57:36,020
Maybe, at the end, he was happy.

